---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout title="Now" description="What I'm currently focused on.">
  <section class="py-[var(--space-section)]">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-[var(--max-w-content)] px-6">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-2">What I'm Doing Now</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-muted mb-10">Updated June 2026</p>

      <div class="prose max-w-2xl">
        <p>
          This is a <a href="https://nownownow.com/about">/now page</a>.
          It tells you what I'm focused on at this point in my life.
        </p>

        <hr class="border-border my-8" />

        <p><strong>Research</strong> — At MIT Senseable City Lab Rio, working on the 3D digital-twin and CFD line — terrestrial LiDAR of favelas fused with aerial multispectral imagery to feed OpenFOAM simulations that map ventilation risk in densely built informal settlements.</p>

        <p><strong>Building</strong> — Just shipped <a href="https://github.com/thrmnn/perception-pipeline">perception-pipeline v0.1</a> (YOLO + ByteTrack baseline, MIT-licensed), consolidating four years of one-off perception code into one modular stack. Also building <a href="https://github.com/thrmnn/agent-harness">agent-harness</a> — typed tools, readable traces, and regression evals for agentic systems.</p>

        <p><strong>Learning</strong> — Following the ETH Zurich Robot Learning course by Oier Mees. Building in public; weekly progress notes.</p>

        <p><strong>Consulting</strong> — Taking a small number of <a href="/consulting/">scoped engagements</a> alongside research: perception pipelines, LiDAR bring-up, and AI-agent infrastructure for teams shipping agentic products.</p>

        <p><strong>Training</strong> — Upper/lower split strength training and Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu.</p>

        <hr class="border-border my-8" />

        <p class="text-sm text-text-muted italic">
          Inspired by <a href="https://sive.rs/nowff">Derek Sivers</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Timeline -->
      <div class="mt-16 max-w-2xl">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-6">Timeline</h2>

        <details open class="mb-4">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-text-primary cursor-pointer py-2">2026</summary>
          <div class="ml-0.5 pl-3 sm:ml-1.5 sm:pl-5 border-l border-border space-y-3 mt-2 text-sm text-text-secondary">
            <p><strong class="text-text-primary">June</strong> — Shipped <a href="https://github.com/thrmnn/perception-pipeline" class="text-[var(--color-link)] hover:text-[var(--color-link-hover)]">perception-pipeline v0.1</a> (YOLO + ByteTrack baseline, MIT-licensed). Opened a small consulting practice for perception and AI-agent infrastructure engagements alongside research.</p>
            <p><strong class="text-text-primary">April</strong> — Started weekly build-in-public updates following ETH Zurich's Robot Learning course (Oier Mees).</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details open class="mb-4">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-text-primary cursor-pointer py-2">2025</summary>
          <div class="ml-0.5 pl-3 sm:ml-1.5 sm:pl-5 border-l border-border space-y-3 mt-2 text-sm text-text-secondary">
            <p><strong class="text-text-primary">January</strong> — Joined MIT Senseable City Lab in Rio de Janeiro as founding member of the Rio branch — researcher on urban digital twins for public health.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="mb-4">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-text-primary cursor-pointer py-2">2024</summary>
          <div class="ml-0.5 pl-3 sm:ml-1.5 sm:pl-5 border-l border-border space-y-3 mt-2 text-sm text-text-secondary">
            <p><strong class="text-text-primary">September</strong> — Defended Master's thesis at EPFL: Urban Tree Morphology and Canopy Density Estimation from Aerial LiDAR, conducted at MIT Senseable City Lab Amsterdam.</p>
            <p><strong class="text-text-primary">March</strong> — Joined Roboat (MIT spinoff) as first engineering hire. Built end-to-end perception system for autonomous vessels in Amsterdam.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="mb-4">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-text-primary cursor-pointer py-2">2023</summary>
          <div class="ml-0.5 pl-3 sm:ml-1.5 sm:pl-5 border-l border-border space-y-3 mt-2 text-sm text-text-secondary">
            <p><strong class="text-text-primary">October</strong> — Started visiting research at IRI (CSIC-UPC), Barcelona, on event cameras for high-speed drone state estimation.</p>
            <p><strong class="text-text-primary">June</strong> — Completed research assistantship at EPFL VITA Lab, building an open-source ROS autonomy stack for mobile robot navigation.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="mb-4">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-text-primary cursor-pointer py-2">2022</summary>
          <div class="ml-0.5 pl-3 sm:ml-1.5 sm:pl-5 border-l border-border space-y-3 mt-2 text-sm text-text-secondary">
            <p><strong class="text-text-primary">September</strong> — Started as Teaching Assistant at EPFL for General Physics and Mobile Robotics.</p>
            <p><strong class="text-text-primary">June</strong> — Joined VITA Lab at EPFL as Research Assistant under Dr. Alexandre Alahi.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="mb-4">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-text-primary cursor-pointer py-2">2021</summary>
          <div class="ml-0.5 pl-3 sm:ml-1.5 sm:pl-5 border-l border-border space-y-3 mt-2 text-sm text-text-secondary">
            <p><strong class="text-text-primary">September</strong> — Started MSc in Robotics at EPFL.</p>
            <p><strong class="text-text-primary">June</strong> — Completed exchange year at KTH Royal Institute of Technology, Stockholm.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
